    "RepaymentMethod": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Repayment method defines how interest is treated across the lifecycle (origination, accrual, due/payment, settlement, default).\r\n\r\nDue Method\r\nInterest is charged only on the outstanding principal and becomes payable separately when due.\r\n\r\nIf the borrower doesnt pay interest immediately, it remains as an unpaid due but does not itself generate further interest.\r\n\r\n\r\nCapitalization Method\r\nUnpaid interest is added to the principal, and future interest is charged on this increased amount.\r\n\r\nLeads to compound interest, where debt can grow faster if payments are delayed",
      "x-status": "stable",
      "x-modified-by": null,
